\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16060283 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \f38\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp2057 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16060283 1st ARMOURED DIVISION
\par MORALE REPORT
\par For period 1 May \emdash  30 Sep 47
\par 
\par 1. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 (a) Main Features}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283  
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li426\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin426\itap0\pararsid10164406 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
Since 1 May 47 the whole Division has been subject to much movement. May and June and part of Jul
y were spent in moving the greater part of the Division from ITALY to join the RA Group in EGYPT, end later to deploy in PALESTINE Despite many changes in plan and location - acme units have changed location two or three times in as many months - morale o
n the whole is good.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 The news of the impending dispersal of the Divisio}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 n came as a shook to everyone a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
nd brought home to some the seriousness of the state of affairs at home.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 The feeling of uncertainty as regards the future affects the Regular Officer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid942680  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
more than any other category and is an adverse factor towards morale.
\par The recent talk by the DRAC (26 Sep) to the officers, warrant officers and senior NOOs of 2 Armd Bde, outlining the new proposals for the reorganisation of the JAC, had a very beneficial effect in this respect.
\par 
\par (b) Att}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 itude towards local inhabitants.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par In EGYPT the general attitude of the troops to the locals is one of tolerant contempt coupled with a feeling of suspicion towards the shopkeepers and contractors.
\par In PAL
ESTINE the Jews, depending on the prevailing state of dissident activity, are either distrusted or hated. The feelings aroused after the murder of Sgts MARTIN and PAICE have had time to die down A smell minority have a certain amount of sympathy for the J
ewish cause.
\par The attitude towards the Arab in PALESTINE is one of friendly tolerance. 
\par 
\par (c) Confidence in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406  military and political leaders.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li851\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin851\itap0\pararsid10164406 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 (i) Military
\par Apart from those who served in the war the average soldier has a distressingly smell knowledge of who the military lenders are, and displays very little interest in any commander above divisional level. Up to this level there is general confidence.
\par 
\par The difficulties of the higher military leaders are appreciated by the majority of officers end senior other ranks.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid942680  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
'Though perhaps disturbed by a lack of published policy this factor does not have large adverse a feet on morale.
\par 
\par In general confidence in military leaders is good.
\par 
\par (ii) Political 
\par The young soldier of today takes very little interest in Political or home Affairs. The general attitude appears to be that the present Government is doing as well as any other could under the circumstances. Most men would back it again because they feel 
it is the 'Working Man's Party', and will continue to do so until such time as its failure should hit them personally.
\par 
\par The recent announcement concerning direction of labour was received with adverse comments by many soldiers, particularly those nearing release.
\par 
\par (iii) General outlook regarding conditions at home and future prospects}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li426\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin426\itap0\pararsid10164406 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
The minority have been shaken by the news of the financial crisis and the consequent further restrictions in food and clothing at home. The majority, on the other hand,
 take very little interest, and are not aware of the seriousness of the state of affairs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 With very little thought for the future their target in life is to be released from the bondage of the Army and to get back to the freedom (sic) of English home life.
 There is little or no tendency to sign on or to defer release.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16060283 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 2. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 DISCIPLINE }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 Has been mainly good. Whereas in ITALY the moat prevalent serious offence was stealing WD property, in PALESTINE it is sleeping on guard. In the many units who have man
aged to avoid cases of sleeping on guard there has been a refreshing absence of crime.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 The young men of today, whither he be officer, NCO or Private soldier, lacks to a large degree a sense of duty and self-discipline, This is undoubtedly due to the st
range conditions of upbringing during the war years and will take time to eradicate.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 To get back to pre\emdash war standards of discipline a unit needs a strong cadre of regular officers and NCOs. The young emergency commissioned officer, and the junior NCO (
who is unavoidably young and inexperienced) appear to have difficulty in checking men without causing resentment, and they nuke their task more difficult by over familiarity with those whom it is their duty to control. Such regulars as there are do their 
beat, but they are far outnumbered by the host of unenthusiastic temporary soldiers who look forward to nothing but the day of their release.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 As usual, an enormous burden of responsibility rests on and is ably borne by the commanding officer.
\par 
\par 3. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN ALL RANKS, AND WITH OTHER SERVICES AND ALLIED FORCES }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li426\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin426\itap0\pararsid10164406 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 (a) All ranks}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 The relationship between all ranks is good, but with the tendency as mentioned above to over familiarity between junior officers, NCOs and men.
\par 
\par (b) Other servi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 ces. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 There has been no contact with the Royal Navy, and practically none with the RAP.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 There has been a certain amount of liaison with the PALESTINE Police, with whom relations are excellent.
\par 
\par (c) Allied Forces}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 In}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid942680  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 EGYPT the POLES are heartily disliked.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 In PALESTINE there has been little or no contact with Allied Forces.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16060283 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 4. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 MORALE OF SPECIAL CATEGORIES }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li426\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin426\itap0\pararsid10164406 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 (a) Officers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 On the whole good; but the uncertainty of what the future holds is more detrimental to the morale of the regular officer than to any other category.
\par 
\par The fact that many, if not most, have been separated from their families for the greater part of their married lives can only be damaging to morale unfortunately in many uses there is still no indication of this situation being rectified.
\par 
\par (b) Trained Men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 Have settled down in their new surroundings quite well, but are only now beginning to learn to
 make themselves comfortable and organise their own recreation and hobbies.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 The senior and regular NCOs to a large extent have to 'carry' the others.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 The non-regular junior Irks end men in many cases are hypnotised by the thought of release.
\par 
\par (c) Reinforcements}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
Few have been received since the Division arrived in ULF. Those that have arrived are on the whole cheerful and keen, but bewildered. Mot having been brought up in an atmosphere of family and they take time to understand the meaning
 and necessity of Army discipline.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16060283 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 5.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid942680  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 OPERATION OF PYTHON SCHEME AND LEAVE SCHEMES }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li284\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin284\itap0\pararsid10164406 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 (a) Python}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 Satisfactory.
\par 
\par (b) LIAP}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 Satisfactory. The cutting down of vacancies so that virtually only the Regular or short Services Regular is eligible is acc
epted as fair and sensible. Very few non-regulars would in any case have had enough service remaining before Release to have warranted the long trip home.
\par 
\par (c) Local Leave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 There have been varied reports on CYPRUS.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid942680  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
Some leave camps- particularly Golden Sands - are good and much appreciated. Others are bad and have resulted in justified unfavourable comments.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16060283 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par The difficulties of setting up new leave camps within reasonable distance of troops in PALESTINE are appreciated, but under present conditions the need is paramount and the organisation Should be first class.
\par 
\par The relief of being able to get away from the boredom of guard duties and the incessant carrying of arms is almost too obvious to mention. Local leave under current conditions is therefore an enormous factor in raising morale.
\par 
\par 6.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid942680  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 LIVING CONDITIONS INCLUDING ACCOMMODATION, MESSING AND CANTEENS }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li426\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin426\itap0\pararsid10164406 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 (a) accn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 On the whole is satisfactory, but the absence of electric light in the majority of man's tents is a serious defect. The standard issue of one hurricane lamp per tent is quite insufficient, particularly for the coming months.

\par 
\par (b) Messing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 The ration scale, when compared with what is available at home, is good.
\par 
\par As ever, the problem with messing is to find experienced master cooks and Messing officers very few cooks stay long enough to benefit their unite much after being 
sent on courses. Some were impressed into ACC early in their service and have little interest.
\par 
\par Many units have tackled the problem with great energy end have produced good results. In one unit messing is excellent. In a few unite, where the lack of experienced personnel is more marked, the standard of messing is below average.
\par 
\par (c) Canteens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
In EGYPT the canteens are good. In PALESTINE they are quite good, but the prices in NAAFI canteens are much too high, for the goods and service offered.
\par 
\par The Div Amenity Centre and Camp Shopping centres are popular and well patronised, but again the prices are extremely high.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16060283 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 7. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 RECREATION AND ENTERTAINMENT INCLUDING NEWS SERVICE.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li426\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin426\itap0\pararsid10164406 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 (a) Reaction}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 There are plenty of football pitches which are always in use. Many unite have laid out their own athletic grounds and have held sports. Facilities for cricket are poor and far tennis non-existent.
\par 
\par Sea bathing in liable to be hazardous, and the nearest swimming pool is a good hour's drive from the nearest units. On the whole, therefore, facilities are not good.
\par 
\par (b) Entertainment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
Cinemas are sufficient in number and films have been reasonable. There have been a flaw good films and a number of old and poor ones. As ever the complaint is that the prime are too high for the entertainment offered.
\par 
\par CSE live shows are popular, and some hews been first class. More live shows would always be acceptable.
\par 
\par (c) The supply of local newspapers is sometimes erratic. There is a demand for more home newspapers and periodicals.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
The local Forces Broadcasting Station is appreciated.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16060283 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par 8.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid942680  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 MAIL}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 The arrival at mail is apt to be erratic at times. Parcels take longer than they should.
\par 
\par Considerable disgust has been expressed concerning the new postal rates for people writing from home.
\par 
\par 9.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid942680  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 Family Affairs
\par Continued separation from families lovers morale even though it may not produce compassionate cases in this respect one unit \emdash 
 1 BORDER have a legitimate grouse in that since the end of the war they have had families with the unit for only one month, end than only when the unit was in England.
\par The number of compassionate cases has been small. Decisions of the GHQ Compassionate Committee are accepted as fair. Where application for the return of the soldier has emanated from the War Office repatriation has keen speedily dealt with.
\par SSAFA continue to do excellent week.
\par 
\par 10.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid942680  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10164406 EDUCATION}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16060283 
